Will crypto be a new substrate that makes AWS irrelevant? Or Does it do that to Facebook? Maybe. I could give lots of reasons why not, but then there were lots of reasons mobile couldn't make Microsoft irrelevant (indeed, some people still haven't yet accepted that happened)

PCs made IBM just another big tech company. Mobile and the web made Microsoft just another big tech company. This will happen to Google or Amazon as well. 

Unless you think tech progress is over and there'll be no more cycles.

It's not that someone works out how to cross the moat. It's that the castle becomes irrelevant. IBM didn't lose mainframes and Microsoft didn't lose PC operating systems. Instead, those stopped being ways to dominate tech.

With each cycle in tech, companies find ways to build a moat and make a monopoly. Then people look at the moat and think it's invulnerable. They're generally right. IBM still dominates mainframes and Microsoft still dominates PC operating systems and productivity software. But...
